dreisoft.tresos.tresosdb.api.model.v1.swcomponenttemplate.swcinternalbehavior

Interface IRunnableEntity

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IEntity, IExecutableEntity, IIdentifiable

    public interface IRunnableEntity
extends IEntity, IExecutableEntity
    IRunnableEntity: Entity class of the tresosDB model.

    The runnable entities are the smallest code-fragments that are provided by the component and are executed in the RTE. Runnables are for instance set up to respond to data reception or operation invocation on a server.

    GENERATED CODE. DO NOT CHANGE!

      • getCanBeInvokedConcurrently

        boolean getCanBeInvokedConcurrently()
        Query the value of the attribute CanBeInvokedConcurrently.

        Normally, this is FALSE. When this is TRUE, it is allowed that this runnable entity is invoked concurrently (even for one instance of the SW-C), which implies that it is the responsibility of the implementation of the runnable to take care of this form of concurrency.

        Returns:
        The value or null
